wikipedia_page.main: Jack Whelbourne (born 2 August 1991 in Nottingham) is a former British short track speed skater.

link_mentions.page: Nicky Gooch
response: Gooch coaches the Great Britain short track speed skating team. He coaches Elise Christie, Jack Whelbourne, Jon Eley and Charlotte Gilmartin.

link_mentions.page: Chronological summary of the 2014 Winter Olympics
response: *In the men's 1500 metres, Charles Hamelin (Canada) won the gold medal with a time of 2:14.985. Han Tianyu (China) finished second and Viktor Ahn (Russia) finished in third place. The competition began with the qualifying heats, in which the three fastest times were posted by Niels Kerstholt (Netherlands), François Hamelin (Canada) and Thibaut Fauconnet (France), in the 5th heat. In the semifinals, the quickest times were from Charles Hamelin (Canada) and Jack Whelbourne (Great Britain), in heat 3, both qualifying for Final A (the medal round). In Final B (a classification round) Sébastien Lepape (France) finished first.
